As the form stepped forward, the light fell on his features, revealing it not to be a elf at all, but instead a
grinning kobold. The kobold opened his mouth wide, revealing twin rows of pointed teeth, then barked a laugh.

"Oh my," Cody said quietly. As he stared, his hand dropped into his bag, then flicked out toward the kobold. A short,
thin dart suddenly appeared in the neck of the kobold, which gurgled and died. Cody shook his head sadly. "They really
have let this place go downhill."
